  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        patients with multiple myeloma and other related disorders including, without limitation
        to, smoldering myeloma, monoclonal gammopathy of undetermined significance (MGUS), primary
        plasma cell leukemia, solitary plasmacytoma, and amyloidosis
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients must have a diagnosis of multiple myeloma or related malignancy

          2. Patients are undergoing standard of care bone marrow aspirates

          3. Patients (male or female) from any race or ethnicity must be at least 18 years of age
             at the time of registration.

          4. Procedure-specific signed informed consent form prior to initiation of any
             study-related procedures.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. It is the enrolling study physician's discretion to decide if a patient is not fit
             enough to undergo a bone marrow aspirate.

          2. Patients who are incarcerated are not eligible to participate.

          3. Women who are pregnant

          4. Patients who have had another malignancy within the last five (5) years (except for
             basal or squamous cell carcinoma, or in situ cancer of the cervix) where there is a
             possibility to contaminate the bone marrow aspirate.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
